SIMPLE: slapdash
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slapdash
<hw>Slap"dash`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Slap</ets>
+ <ets>dash</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a bold, careless manner;
at random.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With a slap; all at once; slap.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slapdash</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slapdash
<hw>Slap"dash`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To apply, or apply something
to, in a hasty, careless, or rough manner; to roughcast; <as>as, to
<ex>slapdash</ex> mortar or paint on a wall, or to <ex>slapdash</ex> a
wall</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slape</ent>⟦br⟧
